DRAFT C (original preference):
I almost walked past it. No sign I could read, just a smear of light under a curtain and that smell — deep, almost meaty, like something had been quietly insisting on itself for decades. Inside, eight seats, a counter, and an older man who didn't look up. I sat anyway. My Japanese is embarrassing, so I pointed at nothing and hoped. What arrived was a bowl so serious it made me put my phone away, which almost never happens. Thirty years, the woman next to me explained, gesturing at the broth. You could taste the patience. Some places just know exactly what they are.

