DRAFT C (original preference):
The chef set down the first dish — something pale and trembling in a lacquered bowl — and began speaking in the gentlest Japanese I'd ever heard. I nodded. Slowly, with what I hoped read as thoughtful appreciation rather than complete blankness. He continued. I nodded again. At some point my nodding became almost meditative, detached from any actual comprehension, and I found myself just... listening to the sound of his voice instead of the meaning, the way you might listen to rain. The bowl smelled faintly of dashi and something green. Outside, Kyoto was doing its quiet Kyoto thing. I picked up my chopsticks.

